            </form>
            <form type="variant" opt="false">
               <orth xml:lang="jpa" opt="false">עדרבלון</orth>
               <orth type="transliteration" xml:lang="fjb" opt="false">ʿdrblwn</orth>
               <pron notation="rabbinic" opt="false">ʿidravlon</pron>
            </form>
            <sense xml:id="idravlin-dlgenr-1" opt="false">
               <usg type="domain" opt="false">arts</usg>
               <usg type="socioCultural" norm="borrowing" opt="false">cultural borrowing</usg>
               <usg type="normativity" opt="false">standard</usg>
               <usg type="meaningType" opt="false">lit.</usg>
               <usg type="geographic" opt="false"/>
               <cit type="translation" xml:lang="en" subtype="sense">
                  <quote>water-organ or water-organ players</quote>
               </cit>
               <cit type="translationEquivalent" xml:lang="grc">
                  <usg opt="false">
                     <lang opt="false">Post-Classical Greek+</lang>
                  </usg>
                  <quote>ὑδραύλις</quote>
               </cit>
               <cit type="example">
                  <quote xml:lang="jpa">
והיה כמצחק בעיני חתניו אמרו
            <app>
                        <lem>אדרבלין</lem>
                        <rdg wit="#Vat2">אידרבלון</rdg>
                        <rdg wit="#V">אדרכולין</rdg>
                        <rdg wit="#K">הדרבולין</rdg>
                     </app>
 וכרבלין 
במדינה ומדינה נהפכת
         </quote>
                  <bibl default="false" status="draft">
                     <ref type="witness">50,9</ref>
                     <ref type="witness">II 525:5</ref>
                  </bibl>
                  <ref type="entry" xml:lang="jpa" target="koravlin.html">כרבלין</ref>
                  <cit type="translation">
                     <quote xml:lang="en">But he seemed unto his sons-in-law as one that jested. Said they to him: ‘Organ-players and flute-players are in
               the land and the land is to be overthrown?!’ (Freedman / Simon I: 439-440)
            </quote>
                  </cit>
               </cit>
               <cit type="example">
                  <quote xml:lang="jpa">
ושם אחיו יובל הוא היה אבי כל תופש כינור ועוגב
            <app>
                        <lem> עדרבלין</lem>
                        <rdg wit="#Vat2">עדרבלון</rdg>
                        <rdg wit="#Ox2">עדרכלין</rdg>
                        <rdg wit="#K">עדרכלין</rdg>
                     </app>
 וכרבלין
                  </quote>
                  <bibl default="false" status="draft">
                     <ref type="witness">23,3</ref>
                     <ref type="witness">I 223: 5</ref>
                  </bibl>
                  <ref type="entry" xml:lang="jpa" target="koravlin.html">כרבלין</ref>
                  <cit type="translation">
                     <quote xml:lang="en">And his brother’s name was Jubal; he was the father of all such as handle the harp and the pipe:
i. e. organ players and flautists.
            </quote>
                     <bibl default="false" status="draft">Freedman / Simon I: 194</bibl>
                  </cit>
               </cit>
            </sense>
            <etym type="borrowing" opt="false">
               <lbl opt="false">source language</lbl>
               <lang opt="false">Post-Classical Greek+</lang>
               <cit type="etymon" xml:lang="grc">
                  <xr type="related" opt="false">
                     <lbl opt="false">Cf. LSJ</lbl>
                     <ref target="http://www.perseus.tufts.edu/hopper/morph?l=u%28%2Fdr-aulis&amp;la=greek&amp;can=u%28%2Fdr-aulis0"
                          type="entry">ὕδραυλις</ref>
                  </xr>
               </cit>
            </etym>
            <note anchored="true">
Sg. (<term xml:lang="jpa">אדרבלא</term>* <term xml:lang="fjb">ʾrdblʾ</term> |idravlaʾ|) not attested. 
Derived from <term xml:lang="jpa">אדרבליס</term>
               <term xml:lang="fjb">ʾdrblys</term>
 |idravlis|, <term xml:lang="jpa">ארדבליס</term>
               <term xml:lang="fjb">ʾrdblys</term> |irdavlis| (ySuk 5,6 – 55c: 48), 
cf. Krauss II: 13; Levy I: 32,160, Jastrow 18, AC  I: 39; AC VI: 265, or <term xml:lang="jpa">הדראוליס</term>
               <term xml:lang="fjb">hdrʾwlys</term>
 |hudraʾulis| (tAr 1,13), corr. <term xml:lang="jpa">הרדווליס</term>
               <term xml:lang="fjb">hrdwwlys</term> (bAr 10b) - Gr. <term xml:lang="grc">ὕδραυλις</term>, cf. Krauss II: 221, Levi I: 491, Jastrow 365, AC III: 240-241.
   </note>
